---
// Products — the broadcast platform Rose brings to a production.
// Two client-facing services — LIANA + SPICA — running on a shared foundation, Trellis.
// Cross-write surface: CALYX (prose + layout) / SCION (Trellis + build) / SPORE (SPICA + LIANA operate).
// SCION build-side read folded in 2026-07-02: Trellis = foundation band (not a peer product card);
//   keep copy capability-forward, NO availability/uptime/support implication (best-effort homelab infra).
// SPICA card link intentionally omitted — no public demo yet (SPORE TODO).
---

<section id="products">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-label">Products</p>
    <h2>A platform, not just an operator</h2>
    <p class="under-intro">
      Beyond running the desk, I bring a broadcast platform I built and host myself. Two
      client-facing services &mdash; LIANA for live data and graphics, SPICA for rundowns
      and timing &mdash; run on a shared foundation called Trellis, built to fit how shows
      actually run rather than bent around someone else's tool.
    </p>

    <div class="under-grid">

      <div class="card under-card">
        <div class="under-icon">📡</div>
        <div>
          <h3>LIANA</h3>
          <span class="pill sage">Runs on Trellis</span>
          <p>
            A multi-tenant broadcast data CMS. Replaces Google Sheets as the source of
            truth for live show graphics &mdash; rosters, schedules, brackets, head-to-heads,
            and talent predictions, all editable through a web UI and piped straight into
            vMix as live data sources. First tenant: CBLOL UE.
          </p>
          <ul class="under-stack">
            <li><span class="pill">Multi-tenant CMS</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">vMix Data Sources</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">GT Title Designer</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">Live Graphics</span></li>
          </ul>
          <a href="https://trellis.vermilionrose.me/liana/ui/" class="under-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Try the demo &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card under-card">
        <div class="under-icon">📋</div>
        <div>
          <h3>SPICA</h3>
          <span class="pill sage">Runs on Trellis</span>
          <p>
            Broadcast rundowns and show timing. Run-of-show blocks with cascading segment
            timing, a live operator panel for show night, client-scoped rosters, and call
            sheets seeded from them &mdash; the running order, the clock, and the paperwork,
            in the same platform that feeds the graphics.
          </p>
          <ul class="under-stack">
            <li><span class="pill">Rundowns</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">Cascading Timing</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">Live Operator Panel</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">Call Sheets</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">Multi-tenant</span></li>
          </ul>
          {/* No public SPICA demo yet (SPORE TODO). Add the demo link here once /spica/ui/ has public access; until then, no login-walled CTA and no "coming soon" claim. */}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card under-card foundation-card">
        <p class="foundation-label">The foundation</p>
        <div class="under-icon">⚙️</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Trellis</h3>
          <p>
            The platform the rest run on: one API, one identity, many integrations. LIANA
            and SPICA share a single login and database because Trellis gives them that
            &mdash; each integration climbs the same lattice under its own URL prefix, on
            shared auth (accounts, sessions, TOTP MFA), multi-tenancy, and a snapshot-guarded
            deploy pipeline. It began as a tournament API and grew into the platform
            everything else stands on.
          </p>
          <ul class="under-stack">
            <li><span class="pill">FastAPI</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">Neon Postgres</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">Caddy</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">TOTP MFA</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">Multi-tenant</span></li>
          </ul>
          <a href="https://trellis.vermilionrose.me" class="under-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">trellis.vermilionrose.me &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  h2 { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }

  .under-intro {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .under-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(340px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .under-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .under-icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  h3 { margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .pill.sage { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; display: inline-block; }

  .under-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .under-stack {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .under-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--rose);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rose);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    transition: color 120ms ease, border-color 120ms ease;
  }
  .under-link:hover, .under-link:focus {
    color: var(--blush);
    border-bottom-color: var(--blush);
  }

  /* Trellis presented as the substrate the two products stand on — full-width band
     beneath LIANA + SPICA, marked with an eyebrow label rather than a peer-product pill. */
  .foundation-card {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
  }
  .foundation-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.09em;
    color: var(--deep-rose);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
</style>
